<HEADLINE> Greek Troops Leave for Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Last month, the United Nations approved the formation of a
5,000-strong force to secure the speedy distribution of humanitarian
aid to Albania.
</P>
<P>
"Operation Alba" began Tuesday as some 1,200 Italian, French
and Spanish troops arrived in the western port city of Durres and
at Tirana airport to prepare the way for the rest of the
5,000-strong, eight-nation force. 
</P>
