<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 16:00 GMT, April 16 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO -- A tritium leakage has prompted Japan's Power and
Nuclear Fuel Development Corporation (Donen) to shut down an
advanced thermal reactor, local media reported today.
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- More than 10,000 victims of Iraqi chemical warfare
during the 1980-88 war between Iran and Iraq staged a protest
rally in front of the German Embassy this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
NAIROBI -- Zairean rebel leader Laurent Kabila left Lubumbashi,
southern Zaire, today for South Africa to discuss the Zairean
crisis with President Nelson Mandela, a report reaching here this
afternoon said.
</P>
<P>
VALLETTA, MALTA -- The Palestinian National Authority (PNA)
and Israel today promised to return to negotiation table after a
direct high-level meeting brokered by the European Union here.
</P>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY -- The King of Saudi Arabia Fahd Ibn Abdul-Aziz
expressed condolence over the death of those killed, at least 217,
in the fire outside the Holy city of Mecca Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
VALLETTA (MALTA) -- Palestinian National Authority (PNA)
President Yasser Arafat and Israeli Foreign Minister David Levy
met and held talks here today. 
</P>
