<HEADLINE> Kabila Sells Mineral Resources to Americans, S. Africans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Zaire's rebel leader Laurent-Desire
Kabila has signed several contracts with American and South
African mining companies to sell the rich mineral resources of
the southern province of Shaba to them.
</P>
<P>
The rebels' "finance minister" Mawapanga mwana Nanga told
Agence France-Presse (AFP) that they have signed three contracts
with the American Mining Field Corporation (AMFI) and some other
American and South African companies to develop copper and cobalt
fields and open factories in Kolwezi and Kipushi.
</P>
<P>
The Americans will invest 200-220 million U.S. dollars in copper
and cobalt mining projects in Kolwezi, rehabilitate a factory in
Kipushi with 30 million dollars of investment, and create a new
factory in Kipushi to produce and process zinc with an investment of
550-650 million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
