<HEADLINE> Major US Technology Companies Beginning to Recover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Major technology companies in
the United States are beginning to recover from last year's
recession as they reported better-than-expected profits in the
first quarter of this year.
</P>
<P>
The companies which reported earnings that met or surpassed
expectations Tuesday included Texas Instruments Inc., Sun
Microsystems Inc., Cypress Semiconductor Corporation and the LSI
Logic Corporation.
</P>
<P>
The first-quarter earnings at Texas Instruments rose to 138
million U.S. dollars, or 70 cents a share from 132 million
dollars, or 68 cents, a year earlier, topping the Wall Street
consensus of 70 cents. Sun Microsystems had earnings of 224
million U.S. dollars, or 58 cents a share, from 143 million U.S.
dollars, or 37 cents a share, a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
Cypress Semiconductor Corporation and the LSI Logic
Corporation, two other specialized chip makers, also met or beat
analysts' estimates.
</P>
<P>
Texas attributed its higher profits to the transformation from
a commodity chip maker to a producer of specialized,
high-profit-margin chips, known as digital signal processors used
computer components and cellular telephone, among other
applications. And Sun touted its higher profit margins from
powerful network server computers which are enjoying strong demand
in corporate markets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
