<HEADLINE> Kabila to Meet Mnadela, Sahnoun </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Zairean rebel leader Laurent
Kabila is expected to meet South African President Nelson Mandela and
Mahamoud Sahnoun, United Nations Special Envoy to Zaire and the Great
Lakes region, today in Cape Town, said an informed source here.
</P>
<P>
However, there is no official confirmation that Kabila,
scheduled to arrive at Ysterplaat Air Force base near Cape Town
this afternoon, was already in the country, said the source.
</P>
<P>
Although Mandela's office in Cape Town could not confirm Kabila's
arrival, Presidential aide Parks Mankahlana said the president would
meet Kabila should he arrive.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Sahnoun hastily flew to Cape Town from Arusha, Tanzania
after having been informed that Kabila was due in South Africa.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that Kabila left Lubumbashi of Zaire this
morning for South Africa.
</P>
<P>
Kabila told reporters before his departure that he would speak to
Mandela about "the future of my country".
</P>
<P>
While referring to reports that he might hold direct talks with
Zairean President Mobutu Sese Seko in South Africa this week, Kabila
said he did not expect to meet Mobutu during his scheduled two-day's
tour to South Africa.
</P>
<P>
"It is not important for me, Who is he?' said the rebel leader.
