<HEADLINE> EC Supplies Medical Aid to Tajikistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 16 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission has
cleared a package of humanitarian aid worth 900,000 ecus (1.02
million U.S. dollars) to combat an outbreak of typhoid fever in
Tajikistan, the European Community Humanitarian Office(ECHO) said
today,
</P>
<P>
More than 80 people have died, including 50 in the capital
Dushanbe, and an estimated 15,000 have contracted the disease
which broke out earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
Hospitals in Dushanbe are overcrowded and patients have been
admitted to public buildings for treatment.
</P>
<P>
The epidemic could rapidly spread as the climate in the former
Soviet republic warms up as summer approaches.
</P>
<P>
The aid will enable the International Red Cross and
non-governmental organizations from France and Britain to carry
out a six-month program of treatment and preventive action.
</P>
</TEXT>
