<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nemtsov Talks About Russia's Railways Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Russia's state-owned railways
should reduce tariffs for cargo transportation and pay taxes to
the budget in time, First Deputy Prime Minister Boris Nemtsov said
at an extended collegium of the Ministry of the Railways.
</P>
<P>
The Itar-Tass news agency today quoted Nemtsov as saying that
these are the two tasks set for the ministry by President Boris
Yeltsin and Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin.
</P>
<P>
Nemtsov said the railways will be divided into state, regional
and local in the future, and the responsibility will be divided
accordingly.
</P>
<P>
He also said the Ministry of the Railways should stop
bartering, which increase the cost of railway transportation
services by up to 40 percent.
</P>
<P>
Nemtsov today also expressed confidence in the new Minister of
Railways Nikolai Aksenenko, saying he will enable the ministry to
work more effectively.
</P>
<P>
So far, the Russian railways account for three percent of the
country's GNP. 
</P>
</TEXT>
