<HEADLINE> Confederation of Ethiopian Trade Unions to Be </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 16 (Xinhua) -- A congress meant for the re-
establishment of the Confederation of the Ethiopian Trade Unions
(CETU) is to be held in Addis Ababa from April 22 to 24.
</P>
<P>
This was announced here today by the executives of the
coordinating committee for the re-establishment of the CETU.
</P>
<P>
According to the announcement, the three-day congress to be
attended by more than 500 participants is expected to elect
CETU's leadership and members of the audit committee.
</P>
<P>
The congress is also expected to ratify the newly formulated
statute and code of conduct, which provide more autonomy to
member federations and make accountable the president of CETU to
the executive committee.
</P>
<P>
Following the efforts by the coordinating committee since
December, eight trade unions federations representing more than
95 percent of workers have shown interest to join the move.
</P>
<P>
However, the bank and insurance trade union federation has
failed to respond positively in participating in the process.
</P>
<P>
CETU, established by 29 trade unions in 1960s, under the name
"Ethiopian Trade Unions Association", has now 503 member trade
unions. 
</P>
