<HEADLINE> Turkey Decides to Evacuate Embassy Staff from Zaire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Turkey has decided to evacuate
its embassy staff from Kinshasa, capital of Zaire, due to a civil
disorder in that country, a high-ranking Turkish official said
here today.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Ministry Spokesman Omer Akbel told reporters that the
Turkish Embassy in Kinshasa has temporarily suspended its
activities, as the civil disorder, which is going on for a
long period of time, spread to Kinshasa and is threating the
security of the embassy staff.
</P>
<P>
Some spouses of the Turkish personnel working in the
Turkish Embassy in Kinshasa returned to Turkey on March 31,
said Akbel, adding that the remainder would leave Zaire Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that the Turkish Embassy in South Africa
will assume part of the responsibility of the consulate in
Kinshasa. 
