<HEADLINE> 6,900 Join French Communist Party in January </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 16 (Xinhua) -- The French Communist Party (PCF)
admitted 6,900 new members in January 1997, said the PCF in a
communique published today.
</P>
<P>
The PCF claimed a total of 274,862 members at its 29th national
congress held in December in Paris.
</P>
<P>
The party daily ``l'Humanite'' today quoted Marie-Georges
Buffet, member of the national secretariat of the PCF, as saying
that the PCF is admitting an average of 300 new members each week.
</P>
<P>
Among the 96 federations (regional branches) of the PCF, those
of Seine-Saint-Denis and Val-de-Marne, both of them in the working
class suburbs of Paris, had more 20,000 members.
</P>
<P>
The party federations in Bouches-du-Rhone in the south, the
Nord and le Pas-de-Calais northern industrial regions, and
Hauts-de-Seine northwest of Paris have between 10,000 and 20,000
party members.
</P>
<P>
The federation of Paris and nine other federations have between
5,000 and 10,000 members.
</P>
<P>
The daily Le Figaro Tuesday quoted a confidential report of the
PCF as saying that PCF members in Paris dropped by 11 percent from
7,270 in 1994 to 6,450 in 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
