</P>
<P>
--China blocked a U.N. resolution criticizing its human-rights
record for the seventh year in a row. Meanwhile, U.S. Secretary of
State Albright will attend ceremonies on July 1 marking Hong
Kong's transfer to China.
</P>
<P>
The New York Times:
</P>
<P>
--The U.S. Justice Department's inspector general said Tuesday
that the Federal Bureau of Investigation's (FBI)renowed crime
laboratory was riddled with flawed scientific practices that had
potentially tainted dozens of criminal cases, including the
bombings of Federal Building in Oklahoma City and the World Trade
Center in New York.
</P>
<P>
