<HEADLINE> Survey: 3 Million Child Abuse Victims in U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 16 (Xinhua) -- More than three million
children were reported as victims of child abuse and neglect in
1996 in the United States and nearly a million more were confirmed
victims of maltreatment, according to a non-profit group.
</P>
<P>
The Chicago-based National Committee to Prevent Child Abuse
released the results of a nationwide survey Wednesday. It revealed
that 1,046 children, or three children per day, died as a result
of abuse or neglect in the United States last year, the United
Press International reported.
</P>
<P>
Committee research director Deborah Daro contends the survey
shows that child abuse is still a "grave" problem.
</P>
<P>
The study found that 82 percent of the fatalities were among
children under five years old. Some 42 percent were less than a
year old at the time of the deaths.
</P>
<P>
But the group saw evidence that in areas where intensive
prevention programs are in place, the child abuse rates dropped.
</P>
</TEXT>
