<HEADLINE> Bosnian Entities Agree on Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SARAJEVO, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Bosnia's two entities of the
Muslim-Croat federation and the Serb republic today agreed to
cooperate in the fields of industry, energy, trade and
transportation.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was reached during the meeting here between the
federation's prime minister Edhem Bicakcic and his Serb
counterpart, Gojko Klickovic, which was also attended by the
ministers of trade, energy and transportation from both entities.
</P>
<P>
Klickovic said that the trade ministries have been instructed
to prepare a protocol on trade between the two entities by the end
of this month, so that it could be signed by the prime ministers
at their next meeting.
</P>
<P>
The ministries of transportation will prepare a protocol with
the aim to resume the nationwide railway service sometime in May,
particular in the field of goods transportation, so that Bosnia
could be connected with Europe through railway, he said.
</P>
<P>
The ministers of the two governments also discussed joint
projects in the fields of metallurgy, oil refining and food
production, Klickovic added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
