<HEADLINE> Africans Have Poor Access to Contraceptive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Poor access to contraceptive
methods has been identified as a key obstacle to the family
planning and the improvement of women's health in the developing
countries especially in African states.
</P>
<P>
Population Action International (PAI) said here today although
the availability of contraception has rosen by nearly three-fold
in Africa since 1982, African couples have poorer access to
contraceptive methods than those in Latin America and Asia.
</P>
<P>
A recent study by PAI shows that over 100 million women of
child-bearing age in the developing countries are believed to
have unmet need for family planning.
</P>
<P>
The study shows that up to a third of African women have an
unmet need for family planning. 
</P>
</TEXT>
