<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nepal PM Calls for Consensus on Water Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Prime Minister Lokendra Bahadur
Chand today called for consensus among Nepal's political parties
to work out a strategy for developing the country's vast water
resource.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a national workshop on "Water Resources Strategy
Formulation" here, Chand said his government's commitment to water
resources development had been made public in its policy program
released recently.
</P>
<P>
The government will continue with the good work initiated in
the past, Chand said, referring to a Nepal-India treaty on the
development of a border river, which was ratified by Nepal's
parliament last September.
</P>
<P>
The Nepali government has formed a national steering committee
to formulate policies to properly utilize the country's abundant
water resources, the prime minister told the workshop.
</P>
<P>
The committee, with representatives from concerned ministries,
will complete its task of working out the country's strategy for
water resources development in two phases, official sources said.
</P>
<P>
It will finally come up with working policies for optimum water
resources development after formulating national objectives and
studying the projects launched in the past, they explained.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
