<HEADLINE> Italian FM Calls for Overall Rehabilitation in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Italian Foreign Minister Lamberto
Dini has stressed that emergency humanitarian aid to Albania must
be accompanied by an initiative for an overall rehabilitation of
the country's economic and financial system, papers reported today.
</P>
<P>
Italy plans to convene an international conference as soon as
possible on achieving stability in Albania, Dini told a joint
meeting of the Senate foreign affairs and defense committees on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
International financial institutions including the World Bank
and the International Monetary Fund, the European Commission and
the Albanian authorities will be invited to attend the conference,
said Dini.
</P>
<P>
A U.N.-authorized multinational protection force led by Italy,
started being deployed in Albania on April 14 to protect
aid supplies to the crisis-hit country.
</P>
<P>
Albania descended into chaos in early March when protests
triggered by the collapse of pyramid-investment schemes, in which
thousands of people lost their life savings, mushroomed across the
country.
</P>
<P>
The protests turned violent after armed rebels looted army
depots and took over several towns in the south.
</P>
<P>
More than 13,000 refugees fled the country in March and the
Albanian government has called for international aid and military
intervention to help the new government of national reconciliation
restore order in the country and prepare for general elections in
June. 
</P>
</TEXT>
