<HEADLINE> China's Accession to WTO in Everyone's Interest: Ruggiero </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Having China in the World Trade
Organization (WTO) is in everyone's interests, WTO
Director-General Renato Ruggiero said today.
</P>
<P>
"China is the world's sixth largest exporter and seventh
largest importer. If we are to be a truly universal organization,
we must bring all the world's trading nations and regions into
this house," Ruggiero, who is to visit China from April 18-23, told
Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
He added that joining the 128-member trade body was also
important for China. "A great power like China does not like to be
outside an organization as dynamic as this one."
</P>
<P>
Ruggiero said that the aim of his visit to China was to push
forward the productive results of the third meeting of the
Working Party on China's accession to WTO.
</P>
<P>
The meeting ended here on March 6 with all sides unanimously
calling it positive, constructive and productive.
</P>
<P>
"I very much want to see the progress we made in March continue
later this spring and throughout this year," Ruggiero said.
</P>
</TEXT>
