<HEADLINE> State Capital Injected in CD Production Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, April 17 (Xinhua) -- A compact disc company parented
by the State Development and Investment Corporation and Shenzhen
Xianke Group opened here today.
</P>
<P>
The Shenzhen Xianke Compact Disc Co. Ltd., based on Shenzhen
Xianke Group, received capital from the State Development and
Investment Corporation, a policy-oriented company established
in Beijing in 1995.
</P>
<P>
The new corporation will take the lead in developing and
producing digital video discs (DVDs) in China. It plans to have
the capability of producing eight million DVDs a year.
</P>
<P>
The company also plans to finish developing DVD-R, a
high-density memory disc, in the near future, which would be a
breakthrough in accelerating China's CD industry.
</P>
<P>
Attached to the State Council, the State Development and
Investment Corporation is a wholly state-owned agency with a
registered capital of 5.8 billion yuan. It invests mainly in
policy-oriented projects in energy, transportation, raw
materials, machine-building, and textiles, as well as farming and
forestry sectors.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen Xianke Group is the largest CD producer and service
provider in China. It is capable of producing 6.5 million laser
discs (LDs), compact discs (CDs), CD-ROMs, and video CDs (VCDs)
a year.
</P>
<P>
The new company will make full use of its capital,
technologies, and market. It will be able to annually produce 20
to 25 million CDs, 1.5 million LDs, 1.2 million CD-ROMs, 1,500
programs, and 250,000 VCD players. 
</P>
</TEXT>
