<HEADLINE> Samsung Insurance Office Opens in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Samsung Fire and Marine
Insurance Co. Ltd. opened an office in Shanghai today.
</P>
<P>
This is the second office the company has opened in
China. Samsung opened its first office in Beijing in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Jin-won You, chief representative of the Samsung Shanghai
office, said that the opening of the new office showed Samsung's
determination to explore the Chinese market. Samsung was confident
about its business in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Samsung Fire and Marine Insurance Co. Ltd., which was
established in 1952 and joined the Samsung group in 1958, is the
largest property insurance company in the Republic of Korea (ROK).
</P>
<P>
The volume of business of Samsung Fire and Marine Insurance
Co. Ltd. reached three billion U.S. dollars last year. It has
become the number one insurance company in ROK by owning 23.5
percent of the whole market share.
</P>
<P>
Samsung Fire and Marine Insurance Co. Ltd. has a total asset
value of 3.73 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
ROK enterprises usually invest in east China's Shandong
province and northeast China's three provinces due to geographical
and historical reasons.
</P>
<P>
However, ROK investments are flowing into all of east China
including Shanghai and south China. Provinces and cities
neighboring Shanghai all have big ROK investors. ROK financial
organizations are also attracted by the great market potential.
</P>
<P>
Currently four foreign insurance companies from the United
States, Japan, Canada, and Switzerland are authorized to do
business in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
