<HEADLINE> China to Apply High Technology to Forestry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 17 (Xinhua) -- China will apply more new and
high technologies to forestry to introduce a relatively
comprehensive ecological system in its forest land, a
senior Chinese official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to a group of Chinese forestry scientists this
morning, Vice-Premier Jiang Chunyun called for a new scientific
and technological revolution in the country's forestry sector.
</P>
<P>
"Forestry is an important sector of infrastructure and the
public welfare," he said, "its role cannot be replaced in social
and economic sustainable development."
</P>
<P>
"We must give high priority to planting and taking care of
forests and increase the ratio of forest cover," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Modern biological engineering technology will be studied for
the improvement of tree species," he said. 
