<HEADLINE> Antwerp World Diamond Center Supports HK Jewelry &AMP; Watch Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The Diamond High Council (HRD),
the official trade federation representing the Belgian diamond
trade and industry, is to hold an international conference on the
diamond industry during the Hong Kong Jewelry &AMP; Watch Fair '97 in
September.
</P>
<P>
According to Miller Freeman Asia Ltd., organizer of the Fair
slated for September 3-7 at the Hong Kong Convention and
Exhibition Center, the HRD will hold an Antwerp Gemmological
Updated Conference on the new high-tech development in diamond
manufacturing and grading, and an update in how to identify
treated and synthetic diamonds.
</P>
<P>
As a world leader, Antwerp, and especially the HRD account for
over 50 percent of the world diamond trade, and with an annual
turnover of over 23 billion U.S. dollars, they are also ahead on
diamond research.
</P>
<P>
Joining forces for this conference slated for September 4 in
Hong Kong will be three HRD departments -- the Institute of
Gemology, the Certificates Department and the Diamond Research
Center.
</P>
<P>
The conference aims to get diamond dealers and jewelers updated
and well informed on the development in diamond industry and
related technologies, Miller Freeman said.  
</P>
