<HEADLINE> Gunnell Aims to Win Gold Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 17 (Xinhua) -- British 400 meters hurdler Sally
Gunnell Thursday said that winning gold again is her realistic aim.
</P>
<P>
"I know what it's like to have won gold once and it is my dream
to regain my (1993) title as world champion, " Gunnell was quoted
by a report as saying.
</P>
<P>
Gunnell's bid to be the first woman to retain her 400m hurdles
Olympic title was shattered when a recurrence of an Achilles
injury forced her out of Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
Gunnell was the only woman to hold Olympic, world, Commonwealth
and European titles at the same time. She will take part in the
world championships in Athens this summer.
</P>
<P>
"With a bit of luck and an injury free season there is no
reason why not. I have had a good winter and now I will centre on
the thought of winning in Athens. It is my dream to do so, " she
said. 
</P>
