<HEADLINE> Six Golfers Lead After Philippine Open First Round </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGUIO CITY, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Six golfers, all with
3-under-par 65s, shared the lead after the first round of the 82nd
Philippine Open, one of Asia's oldest golf championships.
</P>
<P>
Only 18 out of the 141 players from 15 countries managed to
break par on the Club John Hay Golf Course in the northern city of
Baguio.
</P>
<P>
Tied for first place were Filipinos Richard Sinfuego (32-33)
and Roger Cabajar (34-31), Germany's Uli Zilg (35-30), Japan's
Shigenobu Hideto (35-30), Australia's Stephen Leaney (35-30), and
America's Tim Straub (35-30), last year's runner-up.
</P>
<P>
Current Asian Tour leader Edward Fryatt of England was among
six players at 67.
</P>
<P>
The 300,000-U.S-Dollar Philippine Open, which began in 1913, is
one of 12 stops on the 1996-1997 Asian Tour.
</P>
<P>
The events end on Sunday. 
</P>
