<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Manila to Host PECC Meeting in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines will host the 13th
meeting of the 21-member Pacific Economic Cooperation Council
(PECC) in 1999, the official Philippine News Agency reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The Philippines was elected as chairman of the PECC at its
meeting in Bali, Indonesia earlier this month, according to the
agency.
</P>
<P>
Former foreign secretary Roberto Romulo, who now chairs the
Philippine Long Distance Telephone Company (PLDT) board, will
formally assume the PECC chairmanship during its 12th meeting in
Santiago, Chile in October this year.
</P>
<P>
The PECC is a private sector-led organization dedicated to
promoting cooperative development initiatives in the Asia-Pacific
region.
</P>
<P>
The PECC enjoys an official observer status in the Asia-Pacific
Economic Cooperation (APEC) forum.
</P>
<P>
The PECC groups Australia, Brunei, Canada, Chile, China,
Colombia, Hong Kong, Indonesia, Japan, South Korea, Malaysia,
Mexico, New Zealand, Peru, the Philippines, Russia, Singapore,
Chinese Taipei, Thailand, the United States and Vietnam.  
</P>
</TEXT>
