<HEADLINE> Beijing Wins Interport Challenge Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Beijing trounced Hong Kong 3-0
to take the third Beijing-Hong Kong Challenge Cup women's soccer
tournament Thursday night, winning its third straight triumph in
the annual interport event.
</P>
<P>
Pressing the local side for the most part of the match, the
taller and tougher Beijing players launched offensives from time
to time. They would have scored more goals had they been more
patient more accurate in shooting.
</P>
<P>
Shang Shan of the visiting team opened the score with a
19th-minute goal in the first half. And she was followed by
teammate Fan Chunling, who added seven minutes later.
</P>
<P>
It was Shang Shan again at the fifth minute in the second half,
when Hong Kong's goalkeeper stopped a shot but was unable to grab
the ball. Shang dashed up to convert the loose ball. 
</P>
