<HEADLINE> HK Faces New Opportunity in Development: Chinese Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's return to her
motherland will provide a new historical opportunity for its
economic development, said Ulanmulun, deputy director of Xinhua
News Agency Hong Kong Branch.
</P>
<P>
At a seminar organized by the Hong Kong Industrial Districts
Industry and Commerce Associations Ltd., Ulanmulun said that apart
from the diligence and intelligence of the Hong Kong people, the
Chinese mainland is a positive factor for Hong Kong's success.
</P>
<P>
He noted that since the 1980s, the reforms and opening up and
the rapid economic growth in the inland areas have boosted the
Hong Kong's prosperity and economic growth.
</P>
<P>
He said Hong Kong has served as a window for China and
introduced huge amounts of capital to the inland areas.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, he said, Hong Kong is also a major market
whereby the enterprises in the inland areas are making use of
foreign funds.
</P>
<P>
About 90 China-funded enterprises or state-owned enterprises on
the mainland have listed on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange, which
has contributed to the enhancement of Hong Kong's status as a
financial center in the world.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics, in 1995 the investment from the
China's inland areas to the non-manufacturing sectors in Hong Kong
reached 104.6 billion HK dollars, an increase of 13.2 percent
over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The inland areas have become the second largest investor in
Hong Kong, next only to Britain.
</P>
<P>
Ulanmulun said that with Hong Kong's return to her motherland,
the economic exchanges between China's inland and Hong Kong will
be expanded and the economic development will have a rising
impact on Hong Kong's economy.
</P>
<P>
He said Hong Kong is no doubt benefiting from the economic
growth in the inland.
</P>
<P>
He said that with the implementation of the principle of "One
Country, Two Systems", Hong Kong will become more prosperous in
the future.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
