<HEADLINE> Chinese President on Sino-Russian Ties (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 17 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin said here
today that his upcoming summit talks with Russian President Boris
Yeltsin will be of great significance, and expressed his
convinction that his trip to Moscow will surely reap positive
results.
</P>
<P>
During an interview with the Russian Itar-Tass news agency
today, Jiang expounded on Sino-Russian relations and the coming
meeting between leaders of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Jiang reiterated that he will soon pay a state visit to Russia
at the invitation of President Yeltsin, and described their summit
as the first summit between the two nations since they decided to
establish a strategic cooperative partnership moving toward the
21st century based on equality and mutual trust.
</P>
<P>
"I will discuss mainly with President Yeltsin ways to promote
the strategic cooperative partnership between our two countries,
and confer on current international situation and international
relations," he said.
</P>
<P>
According to Jiang, they will sign an important political
document to expound in detail the two countries' common ideas and
propositions on the development of the world order.
</P>
<P>
Another important highlight of his visit will be that state
leaders of China, Russia, Kazakhstan, Kirghizstan and Tadzhikistan
will sign an agreement on disarmament along the boundary line,
Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He believed that the agreement will be of profound significance
to the good-neighborly relations between China and the four
countries as well as the peace and stability along the boundary
line, which extends more than 7,000 km.
</P>
<P>
"The coming summit will be of great practical significance, no
matter to the in-depth growth of bilateral ties, or to the
promotion of world multi-polarization or establishment of a
peaceful, stable, just and rational new world order," Jiang noted.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his strong belief that his visit to Moscow is sure
to reap positive results.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the two countries' role in safeguarding world
peace, stability and development, Jiang said that to reinforce
bilateral mutually-beneficial cooperation in political, economic,
trade as well as science, technological and cultural sectors
between China and Russia -- which are close neighbors and
permanent members of the UN Security Council -- will be of benefit
to the peace, stability and development of the Asia-Pacific region
and the world as a whole.
</P>
<P>
Both countries advocate the abandoning of "Cold War Thinking"
and the establishment of a new security concept that will have
universal significance, he said.
</P>
<P>
To realize good-neighborliness, equality and mutual trust,
mutually-beneficial cooperation and common development conforms to
the foundamental and long-term interests of the two countries and
their people, the president added.
</P>
<P>
It also constitutes a concrete move in promoting the new world
situation to comply with the developing trend and demand of the
world situation and international relations, he said.
</P>
<P>
China and Russia, proceeding from their historic responsibility
to ensure world peace, development and the future of mankind,
dedicate themselves to maintaining friendly ties with all other
countries and cooperating equally, with an effort to contribute to
the reinforcement of the world's lasting peace and the common
progress of the mankind.
</P>
</TEXT>
