<HEADLINE> Voter Registration Postpones in Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The Kenya Electoral Commission
has said that the registration of voters for this year's general
election had been delayed due to the lack of computer facilities,
the East African Standard reported today.
</P>
<P>
The daily newspaper quoted the commission Vice-Chairman S.M.
Kivuitu as saying on Wednesday that "it is difficult at the
moment to tell when the exercise will commence and how long it
will last in the absence of supportive facilities."
</P>
<P>
The electoral official pointed out that the commission also
needed sufficient time to train manpower involved in the exercise
before it commences.
</P>
<P>
The registration of voters was scheduled to start on March 1
this year. 
