<HEADLINE> Children's Day Activities to Focus on Moral Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The Working Committee of Women
and Children of the State Council issued a circular here today,
saying that celebrations for the International Children's Day
should focus on moral education.
</P>
<P>
The activities should combine the education on patriotism with
the return of Hong Kong and the 15th Congress of the Chinese
Communist Party, two major political events for this year, said
Zhen Yan, deputy-director of the office of the committee.
</P>
<P>
She said that the activities should be intended to cultivate
the patriotic feeling, and good qualities such as uniting and
helping others and taking an active part in public affairs.
</P>
<P>
They should also be designed to be both instructive and
entertaining in order to broaden children's minds and improve
their abilities, she added.
</P>
<P>
During the period around Children's Day, or June 1, all kinds
of colorful activities will be held by the State Council,
government departments and other organizations in accordance with
the spirit of the circular.
</P>
<P>
On the eve of the Children's Day, more than 200 children from
China's inland areas, Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan will give
performances in a party, sponsored by the Chinese Ministry of
Culture and All-China Women's Federation, to commemorate the
return of Hong Kong to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Ministry of Radio, Film and Television and the
Chinese Children's Film Studio will hold the fifth International
Children's Festival. More than a dozen good children's movies will
be shown in Beijing, and about 30,000 middle and primary school
students are expected to attend. 
</P>
