<HEADLINE> Beijing to Host Asian-European Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 17 (Xinhua) -- A group of experts of the
Asian-European Meeting (ASEM) will meet to discuss on
technological cooperation in Beijing from April 24 to 25, Chinese
Foreign Ministry Spokesman Shen Guofang announced here today at a
press conference.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will be sponsored by the Chinese Foreign Ministry
and other departments, Shen said, and Chinese Vice-Foreign
Minister Tang Jiaxuan will preside over the opening meeting and
State Councilor and Director of State Science and Technology
Commission Song Jian will speak for the occasion.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from members of ASEM and the European Union
Commission will attend the meeting and discuss principles and
areas concerning Asian-European technological cooperation, Shen
said. 
