<HEADLINE> Pankratov Beaten in Heats At World Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GOTHENBURG, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Russian world record holder
Denis Pankratov was surprisingly eliminated in the heats of the
100 meters butterfly on the first day of the World Short Course
Swimming championships Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Pankratov, who swept two golds in the men's butterfly events at
the Centennial Olympic Games in Atlanta last summer, finished a
modest 11th in 53.48 seconds, 1.7 seconds off his own mark.
</P>
<P>
The butterfly specialist refused to comment on his
disappointing performance afterwards.
</P>
<P>
Local hero Lars Frolander finished first in the heats after
clocking in 52.10 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Pankratov's fellow Russian Constantin Ouchkov also was
eliminated out of the final after took a 10th place in 53.34.
</P>
<P>
Pankratov established his world record time of 51.78 on
February 9 in Paris. 
</P>
