<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Closes Slightly Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar closed
slightly lower against the U.S. dollar today, closing at 77.26
U.S. cents, down from 77.57 cents previously.
</P>
<P>
Since March this year, the majority of analysts had thought
that Australia was at the end of the rate cut cycle and that the
next move in official interest rates would be up sometime between
late 1997 and early 1998.
</P>
<P>
But a much weaker-than-expected employment growth shown in data
published last week had some re-float the idea that an easing in
1997 could be in the cards.
</P>
<P>
On the cross-rates, the local unit ended at 96.64, down from
97.80 against the Japanese yen and at 1.3290, down from 1.3398
against the Deutsche mark.  
</P>
