<HEADLINE> Death of Aussie Boxer Under Investigation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 17 (Xinhua) -- A former Australian
heavyweight champion was found dead in his New Mexico home while
his death reason is still under investigation.
</P>
<P>
The body of Craig Petersen was discovered Tuesday and it has
been sent to the medical examiner in Albuquerque, United States.
</P>
<P>
Authorities have not ruled out the possibility of foul play.
</P>
<P>
Born in New Zealand, Petersen grew up in Brisbane,
Australia. He collected a professional record of 22-6 with one
draw. His last fight was on January 28 at Auburn Hills, United
States. He was stopped in the sixth round by unbeaten Chris Byrd.
</P>
<P>
The tough Australian once was thrown into the prison after a
barroom fight with an off-duty police officer in Australia. He
also had problems with alcohol. 
</P>
