<HEADLINE> Slower Growth Predicted for Savings Deposits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The growth in savings deposits
are expected to drop by 7.4 percentage points this year compared
to last year, according to an analytic report by the State
Information Center.
</P>
<P>
The center also estimated the total savings at 4702 billion
yuan this year, an increase of 886.9 billion yuan, or 22.5 percent
over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The annual increase rate stood at 29.9 percent last year over
1995.
</P>
<P>
The two interests rate cuts last year and the low
inflation-beating subsidy rate resulted in a drastic drop in the
savings, according to the report.  
</P>
</TEXT>
