<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Negotiation, or Separatism in Name of Negotiation? (5) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
To play the nasty trick in negotiations, the Dalai Lama claims
that he is only asking for "autonomy," in an attempt to mislead
the public.
</P>
<P>
The system of regional autonomy for ethnic minorities has in
fact been in place in the Tibet Autonomous Region for more than 30
years. Under this system, the Tibetan people enjoy various rights,
which they never enjoyed in old Tibet under the Dalai Lama's rule.
</P>
<P>
The "autonomy" the Dalai Lama asks for can only be the rule by
him and other former serf owners, who followed him into exile, and
be, in their words, "realizing autonomy that will move in the
direction of independence."
</P>
<P>
It is also absurd for the Dalai Lama to ask for practicing
"one country, two systems" in Tibet. Does this mean the Tibet
should restore the old feudal serfdom, which dominated old
Tibet with a combination of religion and politics, and which was
abolished during the democratic reform in 1959?
</P>
<P>
It is odder still that the Dalai Lama flaunts him in pursuit of
"democracy" and "freedom" and claims that "democracy" and
"freedom" should be restored in Tibet. How could there have been
democracy and freedom in old Tibet, where the Dalai Lama, the
chief representative of the three categories of manorial lords,
the former Tibet local government and the monasteries and
nobility, exercised savage and dark rule by feudal serf owners?
</P>
<P>
The fact that Dalai Lama, who sets himself up as a defender of
"democracy" and "freedom," constitutes a gross mock at democracy
and freedom.
</P>
<P>
Facts gathered from his speech and from his acts show that the
Dalai Lama is insincere in his desire to negotiate with China's
central government. He does not show the slightest sincerity for
negotiation. That he claims that he wants to negotate with the
central government is a mere pretext to deceive the public opinion
and gain sympathy by cheating, and a nasty trick to escalate his
activities to split the motherland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
