<TEXT>
<P>
ISTANBUL, April 17 (Xinhua) -- FIBA has fined Turkey's Tofas
about 30,000 U.S. dollars for the incident after the Korac Cup
final earlier this month.
</P>
<P>
The fans of the Turkish squad angered after their team's loss
to Greek team Aris Salonica on April 3 in Bursa, western city of
Turkey and threw coins and woods onto the court.
</P>
<P>
No one was injured in the incidents, which erupted in the final
minutes of the match. Aris Salonica won 88-70 for the title.
</P>
<P>
Basketball's world governing body FIBA also ruled that fans
will be barred from attending Tofas' next two matches.
</P>
<P>
Efe Aydan, general manager of the Tofas, said that they would
appeal against the case at FIBA.
</P>
<P>
Last year another Korac cup game between Aris Salonica and
Turkey's Efes Pilsen team was abandoned after a brawl broke out
between rival players. That match was replayed in an empty arena.
