<HEADLINE> 6,300 Reporters Apply for HK's Handover Ceremony </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 17 (Xinhua) -- More than 6,300 journalists
have handed in application forms for the coverage of Hong Kong's
handover ceremony, according to the latest statistics from the
Hong Kong-based Handover Ceremony Co-ordination Office.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman of the office said that the journalists represent
more than 400 media organizations from almost all countries and
regions in the world.
</P>
<P>
He said that the statistical work for the application is still
going on and the final figure is expected to be published next
week.
</P>
<P>
The Handover Ceremony Co-ordination Office began to accept the
application forms on March 15 and ended the work on April 7.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that due to the limit of the space for the
handover ceremony, the office will allocate quota to media
organizations for the coverage of the ceremony. 
</P>
