<HEADLINE> CPPCC Vice-Chairman Meets Australia Democrats Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Chairman of the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC) Wan Guoquan met with the leader of the
Australia Democrats Cheryl Kernot here today.
</P>
<P>
During their meeting before a dinner, Wan said that the
Sino-Australian relationship has been advancing along a generally
smooth path since the two countries set up diplomatic relations 25
years ago.
</P>
<P>
He said that bilateral economic and trade cooperations have
been growing rapidly due to the high complementarity between the
two economies.
</P>
<P>
China places great importance on the development of the
friendly relations of cooperation with Australia and is ready to
expand cooperation on all levels, he said.
</P>
<P>
He also briefed Kernot about the operation of the CPPCC, a
national representative body of all political parties and
individuals in China. CPPCC serves as an adviser and watchdog to
the central government and the Communist Party of China (CPC).
</P>
<P>
Wan is one of the 25 vice-chairpersons of the CPPCC National
Committee. He is also Vice-President of the Chinese Association
for International Understanding (CAIU).
</P>
<P>
Kernot said that China's reform, opening up, and modernization
drive are very impressive. She wishes that China will secure
faster growth in all fields including economic and social
development. The two countries will further promote contact
between their parliaments and peoples, she said.
</P>
<P>
Kernot, on her third trip to China since 1989, is here as guest
of the CAIU.  
</P>
</TEXT>
