<HEADLINE> Becker out of Men's Singles at Japan Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 17 (Xinhua) -- German star Boris Becker succumbed
to injury again Thursday in the third round of the Japan Open
tennis tournament as he was beaten by Frenchman Lionel Roux.
</P>
<P>
Second-seeded Becker, playing his first tournament since
rupturing a wrist tendon, pulled his right thigh muscle while
leading 16th-seeded Roux 6-4, 2-0. Roux went on to win 4-6, 6-3,
6-1.
</P>
<P>
But Becker said the tendon injury had not been a problem during
his one doubles and two singles matches in the tournament.
</P>
<P>
"The main concern was always my wrist, which is fine right
now," Becker was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Earlier Thursday, top seed and Wimbledon champion Richard
Krajicek beat 15th seed Magnus Norman of Sweden 7-5, 6-0 after
leading 3-1 in the first set.
</P>
<P>
In the women's quarter-finals, fourth seed Ai Sugiyama beat
American Corina Morariu 7-6, 6-2. Sugiyama faces number one seed
Kimberly Po while third seeded American Amy Frazier will play
against Australian wild card Annabel Ellwood in Friday's
semifinals.  
</P>
