<HEADLINE> Record-breaking PATA Travel Mart Held in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 17 (Xinhua) -- An international travel fair held
by the Pacific Asia Travel Association (PATA) for the first time
in China is drawing a record number of participants who are
showing growing interest in Pacific Asia travel products and in
China as a destination.
</P>
<P>
Preliminary figures show that the 20th PATA Travel Mart,
officially opened today in China World Trade Center in Beijing
attracted 471 both holders and some 489 travel product buyers,
representing about 60 countries and regions, with a total of 1,650
delegates registered.
</P>
<P>
The figure surpassed the previous record set last year in
Pattaya, Thailand, which featured 452 exhibitors and 1,448
participants.
</P>
<P>
"The strength of this year's Mart comes from the broad-base
support from throughout the region, and shows the growing interest
in Pacific Asia travel products and the industry's interest in
China as a destination", commented Milton Cooke, PATA Director of
Marketing.
</P>
<P>
The China Host Committee has done an outstanding job in
incorporating the PATA event into the "Visit China 97"
celebration, Mr. Cooke said.
</P>
<P>
While it is the first PATA Mart to be held in China, it will
also be the final year the event changes venue each year, opting
for a permanent location at the Suntec Exhibition Center in
Singapore in 1998, according to sources.
</P>
<P>
"The consecutive record-setting Marts serve as a strong
build-up to the move to Singapore, which will allow us to
eventually double the existing size", Mr. Cooke said.
</P>
<P>
The China National Tourism Administration became an official
member of PATA, an influential non-government organization based
in San Francisco, in 1993, followed by 35 Chinese travel agencies,
hotels, and airlines.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
