<HEADLINE> Singapore, Egypt Sign Pact on Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Singapore and Egypt signed here
today a memorandum of understanding (MOU) on economic, trade, and
investment cooperation to expand the existing "good relations"
between the two countries, the Singapore Ministry of Trade and
Industry said.
</P>
<P>
Under the MOU, both governments agreed to increase efforts to
promote the cross-flow of investment between the two countries and
to facilitate their respective private sectors to establish joint
ventures and collaboration in areas that have potential.
</P>
<P>
The two governments also agreed to cooperate in human resource
training activities in the areas of productivity, trade promotion,
port management and civil aviation.
</P>
<P>
In the area of regional and international cooperation, the two
countries emphasized their willingness to cooperate closely on
issues of common concern in various regional and international
fora like the United Nations and Non-Aligned Movement and at
international conferences.
</P>
<P>
The MOU was signed by Singapore Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong
and his Egyptian counterpart, Kamal Al-Ganzoury, who arrived here
on Tuesday for a three-day official visit to Singapore, the first
by an Egyptian prime minister.  
</P>
</TEXT>
