<HEADLINE> 500 Ugandan Men Receive Vasectomy Operations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Some 500 Ugandan men have
received vasectomy operations, an expert said here yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Doctor Henry Kakande of the Mulago hospital estimated that some 200
men go into hospital for the operation every year, ''the Monitor''
reported today.
</P>
<P>
Kakande has carried out the operation for people without
propoganda.
</P>
<P>
Vasectomy as a family planning measure was introduced into Uganda
in the late 1980s. It involves cutting and blocking
the spermaducts so as to prevent men's seeds from being part of
the semen on ejaculation.
</P>
<P>
Some 70 percent of the men who have had the operations are
educated people, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
Vasectomy is an almost free service in government hospitals.
Five government hospitals in Uganda provide such services, the
report said. enditem

