<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Total prize money of the Wimbledon
Tennis Championship this year will surpass the 10 million
U.S. dollars for the first time.
</P>
<P>
The total money will be increased by 6.5 percent to 11.223
million U.S. dollars at the present exchange rate, Wimbledon
officials announced Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The men's champion will receive 676,450 U.S. dollars and the
women's winner will get 608,805 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
There would be no changes this year to try to slow down the
grass-court game, which has been criticized as being dominated by
power hitters and big servers, All England Club chairman John
Curry was quoted as saying. He also said the same softer balls
from last year would be used again.
</P>
<P>
It was also reported that that construction of the new No. 1
Court was nearly completed and will be ready for the start of the
June 23-July 7 tournament. 
