<DOCNO> XIE19970417.0161 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-17 11:46 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Former Israeli President Chaim Herzog Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Former Israeli president Chaim
Herzog died of pneumonia in hospital today, according to a
Foreign Ministry statement.
</P>
<P>
Herzog was born in Ireland in 1978 and immigrated to
Palestine in 1935. He served in the British army in World
War ii, becoming head of intelligence in northern Germany and
participating in the liberation of the concentration camps.
</P>
<P>
After the establishment of the State of Israel in 1948,
he served as defense attache in Washington. He retired from
the army in 1962 with the rank of major-general, and engaged
in business and law.
</P>
<P>
During the War of June 5, 1967, Herzog was the leading
military commentator on Israel Radio, and afterwards became the
first military governor of the occupied West Bank.
</P>
<P>
He was appointed Israel's ambassador to the U.N. from
1975-78. He was elected to the Knesset (parliament) on the
Labor Party ticket in 1981, serving until 1983.
</P>
<P>
Chaim Herzog was chosen as the sixth president of Israel
in 1983 and served two terms until 1993.
</P>
<P>
After the establishment of diplomatic relations between Israel
and China on January 24, 1992, he was invited to Beijing
in December, becoming first Israeli president to visit China.
</P>
<P>
He took an active part in the activities of the Council
for Promoting Israel-China Relations after it was established
in Tel Aviv in 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970417.0162 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Quarterly Revenues Exceed Spending </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Revenues were greater than
expenditures in the first quarter of this year in China, the
Ministry of Finance said here today.
</P>
<P>
Revenues grew 29.3 percent on a yearly basis while expenditures
rose 18.3 percent, the ministry announced.
</P>
<P>
Consumer and value-added taxes, two major parts of China's tax
measures introduced in 1994, were 20.1 percent more than a year
ago. Business and personal income taxes were up 13.3 percent and
45.5 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The ministry also said that the issue and payment of treasury
bonds has gone well.
</P>
<P>
In spite of all this, a ministry official urged governments at
all levels and related departments to make a greater effort to
collect delinquent taxes and to pay tax rebates to exporters on
time.
</P>
<P>
"Tax cheats must be stopped and dealt with harshly," he
said. The moderately tight fiscal policy must be resolutely
adhered to and new policies that increase spending and decrease
income must be strictly controlled.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
