<HEADLINE> Macao Making Earnest Efforts for Future: Governor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Macao Governor Vasco Rocha Vieira
said here today that his government is making great efforts for a
bright future of the territory.
</P>
<P>
"All the questions stated in the Sino-Portuguese Joint
Declaration will be solved so that the preparation for the
establishment of the special administrative region will be well
done," said the governor, who returned from a state affairs
meeting with the Portuguese president in Lisbon.
</P>
<P>
He said the government has paid special attention to the
localization of the civil service and is making vigorous efforts
in training local personnel.
</P>
<P>
A certain number of local civil servants who finished training
assumed administrative posts several months ago, marking a new
stage of localization, the governor said.
</P>
<P>
His remarks are in response to a speech by China's Hong Kong
and Macao Affairs Office Director Lu Ping, who said on Monday that
the localization of the civil service, especially of middle and
senior posts, should be quickened.
</P>
<P>
"It takes time to train personnel," the governor said. "The
government has taken positive steps (in the localization of the
civil service). We hope the government can function normally and
the civil servants do their job well."
</P>
<P>
When asked about the worsening security situation in the
territory, the governor said the authorities have paid attention
to this and have urged the police department to better coordinate
its fight against crime.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that local people's confidence in their future will be
increased so that they will participate in transition affairs
actively for a better future of Macao," he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
