<HEADLINE> HK Filmart'97 Attracts Worldwide Exhibitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's first ever film
market in June has so far attracted dozens of international film
and TV companies to participate in, said the Hong Kong Trade
Development Council (TDC), organizer of the fair.
</P>
<P>
The event, Filmart'97, will run from 11 to 13 at the Hong Kong
Convention and Exhibition Center.
</P>
<P>
Local exhibitors confirmed include Golden Harvest
Entertainment, Media Asia Films, China Star (HK) Entertainment
Ltd., Mandarin Films and Southern Film Company Ltd..
</P>
<P>
China Star's marketing executive of International Distribution,
Ms Julianna Wong, said: "There were not many chances for local
films to sell abroad, the upcoming Filmart will be the best
distribution center in Asia for us to sell our products."
</P>
<P>
The company will feature a wide range of the company's
productions since 1994 at the fair.
</P>
<P>
Southern Film Company's assistant distribution manager, Mr Qi
Zhiyong, said: "We would like to take this opportunity to promote
our company's image and widen business contacts." Qi's company is
an agent of the Chinese mainland's films in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
A large delegation from China's Ministry of Radio, Film and
Television is also expected to be present.
</P>
<P>
Co-organized by the Movie Producers and Distributors
Association of Hong Kong, the fair will offer a full range of Hong
Kong and Asian products to buyers from around the world, and is
set to consolidate the territory's position as a regional trading
hub for filming business in Asia, the TDC said.
</P>
<P>
So far the body has received inquiries from more than 300
buyers out of 40 countries and regions. 
</P>
