<HEADLINE> German Bankruptcies Continue to Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The number of corporate bankruptcies
in Germany continued to rise in January following a record high in
1996, according to official data released today.
</P>
<P>
The Federal Statistics Office in Wiesbaden said 2,004 cases of
bankruptcies were registered in the first month of the year, up
7.3 percent from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The office said bankruptcies in January, 1997, increased by 8.3
percent in western Germany and five percent in the eastern part of
the country.
</P>
<P>
Corporate bankruptcies in 1996 totaled 31,471, which was 9.3
percent more than those in 1995 and the fifth record high in a
row. 
</P>
