<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President's Forthcoming Russia Trip Is Significant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The upcoming summit between
Russian President Boris Yeltsin and Chinese President Jiang Zemin
to be held in Moscow later this month will not only benefit the
people of both countries, but will be of world importance.
</P>
<P>
Russian Ambassador to China Igor A. Rogachev told Xinhua here
today that during Jiang's visit to Russia, the two sides are
expected to sign a political declaration signifying the evaluation
of the two countries toward the international situation and
issues, and also their common desire to make the world
multipolar-oriented.
</P>
<P>
Russia and China are opposed to a global single-polar pattern,
power politics and hegemonism, he said, and at the summit leaders
of the two countries will express their wish to ensure the peace,
stability and cooperation of the international community.
</P>
<P>
"As Russia and China are permanent members of the UN Security
Council, importance will be placed on their views and positions
throughout the world," he said.
</P>
<P>
Russia, together with China, Kazakhstan, Kirghizstan and
Tadzhikistan, will sign an agreement in Moscow on the reduction of
military forces along border areas after President Jiang Zemin
ends his official visit to Russia, Rogachev said.
</P>
<P>
On the prospects for Russian-Chinese cooperation, Rogachev
noted, bilateral cooperation in various areas is promising,
bilateral trade volume amounted to seven billion US dollars last
year. The two countries have set a target to raise their trade to
20 billion US dollar-worth in early next century, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Russian Ambassador also expressed the hope that a regular
meeting between Russian Prime Minister Viktor Stepanovich
Chernomyrdin and Chinese Premier Li Peng to be held in Beijing in
the coming summer will advance bilateral cooperation to a new
high.  
</P>
</TEXT>
