<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Defects Found in S. Korean High-Speed Rail Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, April 17 (Xinhua) -- More than 20 percent of the work
done on the 61-kilometer-long section of the Seoul-Pusan
high-speed rail system was found to be defective and in need of
reconstructions or repairs, according to a recent audit.
</P>
<P>
The defects, which range from poor concrete work to more
seriously structural problems, were discovered in an inspection on
the construction work conducted by Wiss, Janney, Elstner
Association (WJE) of the United States.
</P>
<P>
The Korea High Speed Rail Construction Authority (KHRC) paid
2.7 million U.S. dollars for WJE's audit to check the construction
quality of the section, inside and outside, top to bottom, for six
months beginning from August 1 last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
