<HEADLINE> Uganda Military Pursues WNBF Rebel Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 17 (Xinhua) -- A team of military and police
investigators arrived at the north-western district of Arua to
launch an inquire into the whereabouts of the rebel leader of the
West Nile Bank Front (WNBF).
</P>
<P>
Local newspaper "the New Vision" reported today that the main
forces of WNBF, one of the three main rebel groups in Uganda,
have been annihilated last month in southern Sudan.
</P>
<P>
Its 974 members including 144 officers and most of high
command members are under detention of Uganda authorities. But
Juma Oris, its main leader, is still alive and goes into
underground, according to Uganda President Yoweri Museveni,
</P>
<P>
The investigators are to interrogate captive WNBF members,
peruse through their confidential files, and summon several
suspected WNBF collaborators and related civilians.
</P>
<P>
WNBF had some 1,000 members before it lost its main forces.
