<HEADLINE> Thousands of S. Africans Emigrate Each Year: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Thousands of South
Africans, including many professionals and technicians, are
emigrating each year, according to the latest annual report
issued by the South African Department of Home Affairs.
</P>
<P>
The total number of emigrants in South Africa in 1996 was
9,708, the report said, noting that the majority of the people
went to Europe, North and South America.
</P>
<P>
The highest exodus occurred among professional people,
followed by skilled workers in manufacturing and construction,
clerical and merchants and managerial people.
</P>
<P>
The figures relating to the emigration of economically active
people showed a sharp rise of 14.6 percent in 1996 as against
1995.
</P>
<P>
In 1994, there were 10,239 emigrants, compared with 6,398
immigrants, or a loss of 3,837. The losses were 3,661 in 1995 and
4,301 in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Compared with a loss of 3,221 people in 1987, South Africa
gained between 2,000 and 10,000 a year from 1988 to 1993, with
more immigrants than emigrants, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
