<HEADLINE> Colombo Gets Garbage Trucks from Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Colombo, capital city of Sri
Lanka, has got 95 garbage trucks valued at 8.8 million U.S.
dollars under a Japanese grant, according to official sources
today.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that Colombo city has been severely hampered
due to a shortage of clearing trucks.
</P>
