<HEADLINE> Shenzhen's Exports Surge by 13 Percent in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The city of Shenzhen in south
China's Guangdong Province reported a 13 percent rise in exports
which were valued at 5.048 billion U.S. dollars in the first three
months of this year, sources from the city's statistical bureau
say.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, state-owned foreign trade companies exported 530
million US dollar-worth of goods, up 38.6 percent over the same
period last year.
</P>
