<HEADLINE> Henan Forms Expressway Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Work on an expressway linking
Xuchang and Luohe cities in central China's Henan Province started
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
It has brought the total mileage of expressway under
construction in Henan to 173 km, which forms a network with
Zhengzhou, the provincial capital, as the center.
</P>
<P>
The 48.9-km-long four-lane expressway will be built at a cost
of 965 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
It will be part of the trunk line between Beijing in north
China and the Zhuhai Economic Zone in the south, which is to be
completed by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
To date, 294 km of expressways have opened to traffic in
Henan. Two more expressways, one between Anyang and Xinyang and
the other linking Sanmenxia with Shangqiu, are expected to be
operational in the next few years. 
</P>
