<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fast Growth in Foreign Trade in Shanghai's Pudong Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The Pudong New Area in Shanghai
exported 790 million US dollars-worth of goods in the first
quarter of this year, up 37.8 percent from the same period last
year.
</P>
<P>
Pudong now has 560 export-oriented enterprises producing over
10,000 types of textile, electronics, machinery, hardware,
chemical, and farm products annually.
</P>
<P>
These have been sold in over 130 countries and regions. Major
trade partners include Japan, the United States, the Republic of
Korea, Southeast Asian nations, the European Union, and Hong Kong
and Taiwan regions.
</P>
<P>
Pudong has exported 9.86 billion US dollars-worth of products
since it began operation in 1993, accounting for one-fifth of
Shanghai's total exports.
</P>
<P>
Foreign trade companies have been the top exporters, with a
record 1.5 billion US dollars worth of exports last year.
</P>
<P>
Exports of overseas-funded enterprises registered rapid growth
for four consecutive years, with exports worth 480 million US
dollars in 1996, almost double the previous year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
