<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe's Maize Harvest Enough to Meet Local </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwean farmers could harvest
over two million tons of maize this year, enough to meet local
consumption with some left over for export though the harvest
will be below the 2.6 million tons produced last year.
</P>
<P>
According to the Central Statistical Office, the reduction in
the expected tonnage has largely been due to the heavy and
incessant rains which resulted in waterloging and leaching of
soil nutrients.
</P>
<P>
The Grain Marketing Board and private buyers are expected to
pay more than 150 million U.S. Dollars for grains and oil seeds
sold by all farmers this year.
</P>
<P>
Farmers are expected to retain over one million tons for their
own consumption. 
</P>
</TEXT>
