<HEADLINE> Iran Expresses Grief over Fire Incident in Mena </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Iran expressed grief over the
huge blaze that killed more than 300 pilgrims at Mena, near the
holy city of Mecca, Saudi Arabia, an official report said here
today.
</P>
<P>
The state-run Tehran Radio reported this morning that the
cabinet ministers had a meeting on the matter, which was presided
over by Iranian President Akbar Hashemi Rafsanjani on Wednesday
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The ministers also condoled with the bereaved family members
of the victims who died in the fire as well as their respective
governments.
</P>
<P>
The report said that no Iranians were killed in the fire
though more than 70,000 Iranian pilgrims were in Saudi Arabia.
</P>
<P>
Some 7,000 tents belonging to pilgrims from India, Pakistan,
Bangladesh and Malaysia caught fire in Mena on Tuesday morning.
</P>
<P>
The fire started at a bridge linking Mecca and Mena and
spread to Mena, 11 kilometers from Mecca, due to high winds.
</P>
