<HEADLINE> Overseas Investment Increasing to East China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, April 17 (Xinhua) -- More and more overseas investors
are putting their money into Rizhao, a city on the coast of east
China's Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, the city approved 64
overseas-funded projects in 1996. Contracts involved a promised
use of 470 million U.S. dollars, and the actual amount of paid-in
overseas funds was 90 million U.S. dollars in the year, both
showing marked increases over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
While increasing their investment scale, overseas investors are
also trying their luck at funding basic facilities, industrial
projects, and energy and transportation projects, as well as real
estate development schemes in the city, said local officials.
</P>
