<P>
According to highly-placed BNP sources, the opposition party is
likely to hold a demonstration before the CEC's office to press
for Hena's resignation for his alleged partisan role during
elections.
</P>
<P>
The BNP, who on last June lost the general election under CEC
Hena, on February last boycotted the by-elections to three
parliamentary seats alleging that fair elections could not be held
under the "partisan" CEC.
</P>
<P>
However, the by-election in Manikganj-3 constituency, of which
the seat fell vacant due to the death of a BNP member of
Parliament, is to be held. The BNP leaders are "unwilling to let
the confirmed seat go unchallenged," said the sources.
</P>
<P>
"We're willing to contest the Manikganj by-poll but the
partisan CEC must go," BNP Secretary General Abdul Mannan recently
told a press conference.
</P>
<P>
Mannan said he hoped the CEC would resign for the sake of fair
elections. "Otherwise, we will compel the CEC to resign through
massive agitation," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
