<HEADLINE> Russians Keen to Tap Civil Aviation Market in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Russia, which remains the
biggest supplier of military hardware and systems to India, has
started taking keen interest in the country's civil aviation
sector, the Hindustan Times said today.
</P>
<P>
With an eye on the vast growing "open sky" market in India, the
Russians participated in a big way at the International India
Civil and Defense Equipment and Systems Exhibition 1997 held here.
</P>
<P>
Apart from military equipment, the Russians are also offering
small civil aircraft.
</P>
<P>
According to the Hindustan Times, not only the state-run Indian
Airlines, but also a number of private airlines in the country are
interested in buying small aircraft, up to 50 passengers capacity,
for short routes in the plains and hills.
</P>
<P>
After the disintegration of the former Soviet Union, Russia has
joined hands with some foreign companies to develop civil
aircraft, which can be used for cargo as well as military
purposes. 
</P>
