<HEADLINE> Mongolian-Language Movie About Genghis Khan To Be Shown </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Chinese film makers hope a new
Mongolian-language movie about Genghis Khan will attract both
domestic and western audiences.
</P>
<P>
The movie, Ke E Lun and Genghis Khan, scheduled to premiere
domestically in May, is China's first film using the Mongolian
language. It will be subtitled with Chinese and English.
</P>
<P>
Genghis Khan (1162-1227) was one of the most famous conquerors
in China's history. He consolidated nomadic tribes into a unified
Mongolia and then extended his empire from China to Europe's
Adriatic Sea.
</P>
<P>
The movie illustrated how Ke E Lun, Genghis Khan's mother,
nurtured her son and assisted him to unify the Mongolian tribes.
</P>
<P>
"I believe the film will be very competitive in the overseas
market because it's produced by Genghis Khan's descendants in the
land where he had founded an empire, thus it has a special
resonance," said Cheng Jianlin, director of the Inner Mongolia
Film Studio, the movie producer.
</P>
<P>
Cheng said most of the movie's production unit members,
including co-directors and leading actor and actress, are
Mongolian.
</P>
<P>
The ten-million-yuan production will also be shown to
commemorate the 50th anniversary of the establishment of the Inner
Mongolia Autonomous Region this year, Cheng said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
