<HEADLINE> Panama Canal Alternative Study Invited in Colombia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, April 16 (Xinhua) -- The deadline for
companies to hand in studies on a possible new trans-ocean
passage as an alternative to the Panama Canal alternative to
the Colombian government is passed today.
</P>
<P>
In September, the government will put up for tender an
environmental impact study of the passage in the Tapon del Darien
region on the northwestern border to Panama.
</P>
<P>
The government said that the construction of the passage is one
of its priorities and the environmental study will determine
whether or not the link will be a canal or railway.
</P>
<P>
Ecologists oppose the building of a canal, which would join the
Atrato and Truando rivers in the province of Choco, saying it
would jeopardize the biodiversity of Tapon del Darien, a swampy
jungle region.
</P>
<P>
Transportation Minister Carlos Hernan Lopez said the canal
would cost 2.33 billion U.S. dollars. 
</P>
