<HEADLINE> Costa Rica Interested in Banana Exports to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Costa Rica "is very interested
in the Chinese market" for its banana exports, Jorge Sauma,
general manager of the National Banana Corporation (Corbana) told
Xinhua today.
</P>
<P>
He said Corbana had discussed the issue with Yang Wensheng,
Assistant to the Chinese Minister of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation, during his visit here recently.
</P>
<P>
The most important banana markets for Costa Rican are the
United States and Europe, together taking 92 percent of its total
exports.
</P>
<P>
But Costa Rican banana growers are interested in expanding
their markets to eastern Europe, Arab and China.
</P>
<P>
Sauma believed that his country could export about 130,000
boxes of bananas every week to China at a price of about six U.S.
dollars per unit.
</P>
<P>
Costa Rica is the world's second biggest banana producer, only
next to Ecuador. At present, some 50,000 hectares are planted and
nearly 50,000 jobs created directly by banana production. 
