<HEADLINE> UNDP Plans 5-Year Aid Program for Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The U.N. Development Program
(UNDP) is planning a five-year aid program for Sri Lanka,
according to official sources today.
</P>
<P>
The sources said UNDP officials are in close dialogue with the
government on the aid program.
</P>
<P>
The UNDP has given the overall objective of contributing to a
process of sustainable human development aimed at reducing and
eventually eradicating absolute poverty in Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
The main reason for poverty in Sri Lanka is the lack of
employment and other opportunities to earn a living. In addition,
the ongoing ethnic conflict is causing displacement of people and
economic and social hardships for people of all ethnic groups, the
sources noted.
</P>
<P>
Accordingly, they stated, the UNDP will focus its support in
the next five years on programs aimed at stimulating further
growth and job creation at the provincial and district levels in
close cooperation with the private sector and community-based
organizations.
</P>
<P>
Other UNDP efforts will be concentrated on the rehabilitation
of the conflict-affected areas, the sources added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
