<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Crimes Decrease in Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Romania registered 32,000
criminal cases in the first quarter of this year, of which 80
percent or 25,631 were cracked down by the police, said an
official of the Interior Ministry today.
</P>
<P>
Compared with the same period last year, violence decreased by
30 percent, and robbery and burglary, by 6 percent.
</P>
<P>
Among the registered 20,763 economic crimes, many are left over
from the past years, said Teodor Zaha ria, chief of the public
security bureau of the ministry.
</P>
<P>
So far this year, the Romanian police have seized 412 firearms,
15,500 ammunitions, 3,407 kilograms of explosives and 1,365
kilograms of drugs, Zaha ria said.
</P>
<P>
The Bucharest police bureau also revealed that in the same
period the Romanian capital reported 9,760 crimes,
half of them criminal in nature. But the security situation in the
capital is under full control, said the police. 
</P>
</TEXT>
