<HEADLINE> Thailand's Motor Vehicle Sales Down in 1st Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Sales of motor vehicles in
Thailand in the first quarter of this year dipped by 8.9 percent
from the same period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Total vehicle sales, excluding motorcycles, were nearly 130,000
units in the said quarter, according to Toyota Motor (Thailand)
Co.
</P>
<P>
Despite the slow economy, sales of cars were up 6 percent, but
sales of commercial vehicles fell by 14.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
Toyota continued to claim top spot in overall vehicle sales,
with 38,710 units, virtually unchanged from the first quarter of
last year.
</P>
<P>
Toyota Soluna, the budget car launched early last month, kept
Toyota on top in passenger car sales, at 17,073 units, up by 34.4
percent.
</P>
<P>
Sales of vehicles from Europe and South Korea dropped
significantly, according to the Japanese car company's figures.
</P>
<P>
In March alone, sales of all kinds of motor vehicles fell by
10.2 percent from march 1996, to 48,100 units.  
</P>
</TEXT>
