<HEADLINE> North Chinese Free Trade Zone Attracts Foreign Fund </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, April 17 (Xinhua) -- A daily average of three million
US dollars of overseas investment is flowing into the Free Trade
Zone in Tianjin Port this year, as internationally recognized
practices have been adopted in conducting free trade businesses.
</P>
<P>
The zone, established in 1992, has been provided with
facilities for storage of goods, processing, trade, and port
service, similar to most free trade zones worldwide, said San
Xiangjun, director of the Administrative Committee of the zone.
</P>
<P>
Ten foreign automobile companies set up storage and sales
centers in the zone, and sell their products not only in China but
to southeastern Asian countries, Mongolia, and eastern Europe.
</P>
<P>
A Sino-US joint-venture built in the zone two storehouses, one
3,000 sq me and the other 6,000 sq m, in addition to a 90,000-sq-m
open-air yard for goods and containers.
</P>
<P>
An 18,000-meter special railway line has been put into
operation in the zone, and is expected to handle 3,000 trains of
this year, which include 40,000 containers.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Victon Industrial and Trade Co., Ltd. was the
first enterprise to start the processing business in the zone. It
processes high-quality home-made cashmere and exports the products
to Japan, Italy, and the United States. The company is leading the
zone in per-capita profits and hard currency earnings.
</P>
<P>
The majority of the enterprises in the zone are engaged in
foreign trade, making it an international distribution center. As
a result, more than 50 trade companies make an average of 10
million yuan in annual sales and 20 companies each earn 100
million US dollars every year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
