<HEADLINE> Wholesale Markets Enjoy Good Business in Shenyang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Hundreds of thousands of
shoppers from cities near Shenyang, capital of northeast China's
Liaoning Province, and even from Russia, head for the Wu'ai
Wholesale Market each morning to purchase goods.
</P>
<P>
The market, considered the best of its kind in Chinese cities,
covers an area of nearly 200,000 square meters, with 16,000 stands
and 40,000 employees. Its sales volume topped ten billion yuan
last year.
