<HEADLINE> China's Investment in Agriculture Reports Big Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 17 (Xinhua) -- China's investment in its primary
industry, which includes farming, forestry, animal husbandry,
fishery and water conservancy, hit 1.3 billion yuan in the first
two months of this year, up 151.5 percent from the same period of
1996, recent official statistics said.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest statistics from the State Statistical
Bureau, the country's investment in the second industry (industry
and construction) during the January-February period was 22.95
billion yuan, up 12.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
That in the tertiary industry (service trade) reached 34.6
billion yuan, up 19.9 percent from the same period of 1996.
</P>
