<HEADLINE> China Endows Medical Equipment, Medicines to Ukraine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, April 16 (Xinhua) -- China donated medical equipment and
medicines worth 1 million yuan (about 120,000 U.S. dollars)
Wednesday to Ukraine to help it diminish the aftermath of the
Chernobyl disaster.
</P>
<P>
These Medicines and equipment will be given to the Kiev No. 2
Hospital, which is specialized in treating Chernobyl victims.
</P>
<P>
Chernobyl is one of the five nuclear power plants in
Ukraine. Its fourth reactor exploded in April 1986, sending
radioactive cloud across much of Europe.
</P>
<P>
Radiation hurt 3.2 million Ukrainian people, including 950,000
children, and 16,700 residents died in the worst nuclear disaster
on earth.
</P>
<P>
At the presentation ceremony, First Deputy Minister of Emergent
Situations Vladimir Potikha said that Ukraine has to decrease the
consequences of the Chernobyl explosion alone, which should have
been done by the former Soviet Union.
</P>
<P>
He said that China's aid was of great importance to Ukraine,
which does not have enough power to solve the problem by itself.
</P>
</TEXT>
