<HEADLINE> Canadians Lead World Curling Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Both Canadian rinks maintained
their top places after Wednesday's actions at the World Curling
Championships in Bern, Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
Despite a 7-6 loss to Germany, Canada still secured its place
in the semi-finals where Scotland also sailed into after its sixth
straight win of 5-4 over Norway.
</P>
<P>
Scotland and Canada shared the top places of the standings with
an identical 6-2 record.
</P>
<P>
The Canadian women also failed to keep their unbeaten record
intact when they dropped an 8-5 decision to Germany.
</P>
<P>
Later in the day, the two-time world champions defeated Finland
9-6 to take the top spot with a mark of 6-1 as two games remained
in the round robin tournament.
</P>
<P>
In other matches, Scotland lost to Japan 8-5 before nipping the
host Switzerland 12-3, which lost to Norway 9-5 later. 
</P>
