<HEADLINE> Jalabert Takes Fleche Wallone Classic Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Laurent Jalabert of France broke
away from compatriot Luc Leblanc in the last kilometer to win the
Fleche Wallonne cycle race for the second time in three years in
Huy on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Jalabert, of Spanish Once team, dashed through the steep hill
course by finishing about 18 seconds ahead of former world
champion Leblanc.
</P>
<P>
His Swiss teammate Alex Zuelle edged out six other riders to
take the third place.
</P>
<P>
Jalabert, chased by both Leblanc and Italian Enrico Zaina, left
Zaina behind on the penultimate climb and was more than 50 seconds
clear of a group of 20 riders at the start of the 1,300-meter
hill, which had to be climbed three times during the race. 
</P>
