<HEADLINE> Highlights of Major Beijing-Based Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Highlights of today's major
Beijing-based newspapers:
</P>
<P>
 "People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- The Communist Party of China (CPC) reaffirms its commitment
to building a clean and honest government by banning its senior
officials from engaging in personal profit-seeking and other
activities.
</P>
<P>
-- Li Ruihuan, a top CPC leader, has urged other provinces and
regions to continue to provide economic assistance to the Tibet
Autonomous Region. He said yesterday that this is an important
work "directly related to the struggle against the Dalai Lama's
splittist attempts and against international anti-China forces."
</P>
<P>
 "Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- Foreign Ministry Spokesman Shen Guofang urged yesterday the
United States to promptly correct its wrongful decision to provide
Taiwan with F-16 fighter jets. The US made a decision in 1992 to
sell 150 F-16 fighter jets to Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman also expressed China's admiration and gratitude
to countries who supported China's stand at a session of the UN
Commission on Human Rights.
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese President Jiang Zemin met with President of the
Congress of Peru Victor Joyway Rojas, calling him an "old friend
of the Chinese people".
</P>
<P>
-- Another strong earthquake with a magnitude of 6.3 on the
Richter scale hit northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous
Region yesterday.
</P>
<P>
"Beijing Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- The municipal government made a decision to step up the
development of 69 profitable enterprises, with most of them being
state-owned firms.
</P>
<P>
"China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- China is planning to standardize its growing securities
market by learning from international experience. 
</P>
