<HEADLINE> Dow Continues Rallying </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Blue-chip issues rallied for the
third straight session today with the Dow Jones industrial average
jumping 92.71 points to 6,679.87.
</P>
<P>
The Dow rebounded nearly 290 points over the previous three
sessions.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 4-to-3 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, where its volume totaled 498.82
million shares, slightly down from 506.88 million in the previous
session.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list rose 8.81 to 763.53, the
NYSE's composite index rose 4.13 to 401.75, and the American Stock
Exchange composite index rose 1.45 to 556.51.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq market retreated again as the technology and
small-company sectors continued to struggle. The Nasdaq composite
index fell 2.59 to 1,210.29.
</P>
<P>
As bond prices fell earlier today, the yield on the 30-year
Treasury bond once touched 7.15 percent. It dipped to 7.10
percent. On Monday, the long-bond yield rose to a nine-month high
of 7.17 percent. 
</P>
